1
00:00:00,208 --> 00:00:01,960
Do I seem like I'm lying right now?

2
00:00:02,544 --> 00:00:03,461
Young kids these days

3
00:00:03,461 --> 00:00:05,422
have no basic manners!

4
00:00:06,715 --> 00:00:07,340
I'm sorry

5
00:00:07,340 --> 00:00:08,800
I'll talk to the manager

6
00:00:08,883 --> 00:00:10,468
Ugh, what are you even saying!

7
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:12,178
- You can brew the coffee again

8
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:15,306
But

9
00:00:15,890 --> 00:00:17,475
having no basic manners has no solution

10
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:21,479
What are you saying?

11
00:00:21,896 --> 00:00:22,981
Aren't you also a part-timer?

12
00:00:23,648 --> 00:00:25,358
Yes, I'm the part-timer Jun

13
00:00:25,650 --> 00:00:27,277
And this is where my cousin works

14
00:00:29,446 --> 00:00:30,530
Do you realize what you did?

15
00:00:31,239 --> 00:00:33,575
Right now, the problem isn't the coffee

16
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:34,659
You stepped over the line

17
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:37,871
What kind of people are you?

18
00:00:38,121 --> 00:00:39,873
I'm sorry, I'll give you a refund...

19
00:00:40,081 --> 00:00:41,875
Forget it, I just want to talk to the manager

20
00:00:43,668 --> 00:00:45,128
He's out for a sec,

21
00:00:45,336 --> 00:00:45,962
so please talk to me...

22
00:00:46,254 --> 00:00:48,173
I have nothing to say to a kid like you

23
00:00:48,465 --> 00:00:50,550
Or should I file a complaint
with the consumer protection agency?

24
00:00:55,472 --> 00:00:56,681
Kid?

25
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:58,475
He may be a kid to you,

26
00:00:58,475 --> 00:01:00,185
but to me, he's my one and only relative

27
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:03,646
If you shut up and leave now,
I'll let everything you've done slide

28
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:04,481
But

29
00:01:05,148 --> 00:01:06,816
if you're still standing here after five seconds,

30
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:07,567
then...

31
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:10,153
you'll have to drink your coffee
with only one arm

32
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:21,456
Uh...

33
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:24,667
I better get going now

34
00:01:33,676 --> 00:01:34,886
Hey, what are you doing?

35
00:01:35,678 --> 00:01:37,347
You shouldn't say things like that to customers

36
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:40,767
Then from now on, try not to get hurt first

37
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:44,979
I don't like seeing that

38
00:01:48,024 --> 00:01:48,900
Thank you

39
00:01:49,859 --> 00:01:50,485
But

40
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:54,155
please stay quiet from now on

41
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:57,075
I can't do that...

42
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:07,794
because I'm quite intense

43
00:02:29,357 --> 00:02:30,191
You did a great job

44
00:02:33,903 --> 00:02:35,697
Jun, I noticed you're quick and witty!

45
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:38,825
Minu, you've got a good cousin

46
00:02:40,118 --> 00:02:41,744
Since you worked hard today,
let's have a company dinner

47
00:02:42,245 --> 00:02:42,829
You can come, too, Jun

48
00:02:44,038 --> 00:02:44,622
Company dinner?

49
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:46,082
What's that?

50
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:48,543
We're just eating delicious things

51
00:02:48,751 --> 00:02:50,044
Meat or chicken, perhaps?

52
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:52,547
That sounds good

53
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:08,479
Alright, everyone, you've all worked hard today

54
00:03:08,938 --> 00:03:10,064
And Jun, great job on your first day

55
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:12,775
Let's have a drink and relax

56
00:03:14,694 --> 00:03:16,029
But you said it was meat

57
00:03:16,946 --> 00:03:18,031
This is... chicken

58
00:03:18,656 --> 00:03:20,283
and it's fried?

59
00:03:20,992 --> 00:03:22,911
Why are we eating something so disgusting?

60
00:03:24,245 --> 00:03:25,580
It's delicious!

61
00:03:26,581 --> 00:03:27,498
And that part you're holding

62
00:03:27,498 --> 00:03:28,917
is the most delicious

63
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:33,379
Since it's Jun's first time,

64
00:03:33,671 --> 00:03:35,340
I'll make you a proper soju and beer cocktail

65
00:03:55,652 --> 00:03:56,361
Here you go

66
00:03:58,613 --> 00:03:59,781
- What's this?

67
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:04,869
This is the Korean spirit

68
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:07,622
A sharp scent...

69
00:04:08,164 --> 00:04:09,707
Isn't this poison?

70
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:11,626
Somaek

71
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:15,546
A glass filled with the magic of alcohol

72
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:18,758
Just having one glass of this...

73
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:20,343
will change your world

74
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:24,347
Just drink it, you won't die

75
00:04:24,889 --> 00:04:25,556
Ugh...

76
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:42,573
Huh?

77
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:46,452
This is more delicious than I thought

78
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,373
Everyone reacts like that at first,

79
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,625
but you'll end up drinking it more and more

80
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:55,169
Let's have another glass

81
00:05:10,059 --> 00:05:11,394
Drink up

82
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:12,979
Let's drink and die

83
00:05:16,274 --> 00:05:17,400
You see,

84
00:05:18,609 --> 00:05:21,237
I didn't know this was more dangerous than blood

85
00:05:22,739 --> 00:05:24,240
You humans,

86
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:26,451
what the heck are you doing?

87
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:33,458
This... alcohol,

88
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:38,254
it's like magic

89
00:05:39,213 --> 00:05:40,006
that brings

90
00:05:41,382 --> 00:05:42,258
people closer

91
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:42,967
Magic...

92
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:47,013
We are all

93
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:49,015
allies of

94
00:05:50,099 --> 00:05:51,100
this somaek

95
00:05:51,642 --> 00:05:53,644
Ah... allies of somaek

96
00:05:54,937 --> 00:05:56,356
But Jun

97
00:05:59,942 --> 00:06:02,320
You may talk a little strange,

98
00:06:03,696 --> 00:06:04,614
but somehow,

99
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:07,075
I feel a connection

100
00:06:10,286 --> 00:06:12,580
Minu always acts cold,

101
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:14,916
but even he smiled

102
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,585
all day thanks to you

103
00:06:21,714 --> 00:06:22,757
He's adapting really quickly

104
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:24,717
What a strange guy

105
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:39,690
Human world

106
00:06:40,149 --> 00:06:41,025
Cheers!

107
00:06:42,151 --> 00:06:43,694
Chicken and somaek

108
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:46,864
Glory will be theirs!

109
00:06:50,618 --> 00:06:53,871
Wow... Jun, what a good line!

110
00:06:55,456 --> 00:06:57,625
You drink so well, too

111
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:04,298
- Minu

112
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:06,926
Why aren't you drinking this?

113
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:09,637
This is, you see,

114
00:07:10,221 --> 00:07:11,764
liquid that contains

115
00:07:12,473 --> 00:07:14,016
the truth of the world

116
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:16,561
I value tomorrow

117
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:19,355
more than the truth of the world

118
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:22,483
Drink it quietly, and be careful
of a hangover tomorrow

119
00:07:45,089 --> 00:07:45,506
You're...

120
00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:47,008
so cool

121
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:52,346
Among humans,

122
00:07:52,972 --> 00:07:56,184
you seem like the most decent person

123
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:23,044
Stop linking your arm with mine!

124
00:08:23,377 --> 00:08:24,295
Ah... no

125
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,047
We must always be together

126
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:27,590
So,

127
00:08:27,590 --> 00:08:28,508
don't

128
00:08:28,549 --> 00:08:29,717
go anywhere

129
00:08:30,301 --> 00:08:31,052
Got it?

130
00:08:32,303 --> 00:08:33,346
What kind of vampire

131
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:34,597
is this weak with alcohol?

132
00:08:35,681 --> 00:08:36,140
- Huh?

133
00:08:36,557 --> 00:08:37,225
It's a shooting star!

134
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,059
You should make a wish

135
00:08:38,184 --> 00:08:38,643
Where?

136
00:08:38,976 --> 00:08:39,477
Where, where?

137
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:42,897
I made a wish, let's go

138
00:08:42,897 --> 00:08:43,314
Where?

139
00:08:43,314 --> 00:08:43,981
I didn't see it

140
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:45,399
It was right there

141
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:47,276
- Where was it?

142
00:08:47,443 --> 00:08:48,528
- Ah, over there!

143
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:51,572
- Aww... I want to see a shooting star, too
